.TH "HTMLINPUTELEMENT.WEBKITDIRECTORY" "3JS" "September 18, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLInputElement.webkitdirectory \- HTMLInputElement: webkitdirectory
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]webkitdirectory\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLInputElement\f[R] interface reflects the
\f[CR]webkitdirectory\f[R] HTML attribute, which indicates that
\f[CR]<input type=\(dqfile\(dq>\f[R] elements can only select
directories instead of files.
.PP
When a directory is selected, the directory and its entire hierarchy of
contents are included in the set of selected items.
The selected file system entries can be obtained using the
\f[CR]webkitEntries\f[R] property.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This property is called \f[CR]webkitdirectory\f[R] in
the specification due to its origins as a Google Chrome\-specific API.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A Boolean; \f[CR]true\f[R] if the \f[CR]<input>\f[R] element should
allow picking only directories or \f[CR]false\f[R] if only files should
be selectable.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Setting \f[CR]webkitdirectory\f[R] to \f[CR]true\f[R] causes the input
element to offer directories for the user to select instead of files.
After the user chooses a directory, each \f[CR]File\f[R] object in the
returned \f[CR]files\f[R] has its \f[CR]File.webkitRelativePath\f[R]
property set to a path relative to the selected ancestor directory.
For example, consider this file system:
.IP
.EX
PhotoAlbums
├── Birthdays
│   ├── Jamie\(aqs 1st birthday
│   │   ├── PIC1000.jpg
│   │   └── PIC1044.jpg
│   └── Don\(aqs 40th birthday
│       ├── PIC2343.jpg
│       └── PIC2356.jpg
└── Vacations
    └── Mars
        ├── PIC5556.jpg
        ├── PIC5684.jpg
        └── PIC5712.jpg
.EE
.PP
If the user chooses the \f[CR]PhotoAlbums\f[R] directory, the list
reported by files will contain \f[CR]File\f[R] objects for every file.
The entry for \f[CR]PIC2343.jpg\f[R] will have a
\f[CR]webkitRelativePath\f[R] of
\f[CR]PhotoAlbums/Birthdays/Don\(aqs 40th birthday/PIC2343.jpg\f[R].
This makes it possible to determine the selected directory\(cqs
hierarchy even though the \f[CR]FileList\f[R] is flat.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The behavior of \f[CR]webkitRelativePath\f[R] is
different in \f[I]Chromium < 72\f[R].
See \c
.UR https://crbug.com/124187
this bug
.UE \c
\ for further details.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
In this example, a directory picker is presented which lets the user
choose one or more directories.
When the \f[CR]change\f[R] event occurs, a list of all files contained
within the selected directory hierarchies is created and displayed.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]input\f[R] type=\(dqfile\(dq id=\(dqfile\-picker\(dq name=\(dqfileList\(dq webkitdirectory multiple />
<\f[B]ul\f[R] id=\(dqlisting\(dq></\f[B]ul\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
document.getElementById(\(dqfile\-picker\(dq).addEventListener(\(dqchange\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]let\f[R] output = document.getElementById(\(dqlisting\(dq);
  \f[B]for\f[R] (\f[B]const\f[R] file \f[B]of\f[R] event.target.files) {
    \f[B]let\f[R] item = document.createElement(\(dqli\(dq);
    item.textContent = file.webkitRelativePath;
    output.appendChild(item);
  }
});
.EE
.SS Result
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
File and Directory Entries API
.IP \(bu 2
